102
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:08,000
 Sometimes life is going to feel unsteady.

103
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:13,000
 So tonight, rather than putting forth an effort to make sure you have a safe life,

104
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:19,000
 I want to propose a better option as putting forth an effort to have a courageously faithful life.

105
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:24,000
 Your goal is not a safe life, but a courageously faithful life.

106
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,000
 And sometimes it won't feel safe.

107
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:31,000
 Sometimes it will feel like you're climbing the monkey bars, and you're looking down going,

108
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:34,000
 "If I fall, it's going to really hurt."

109
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:38,000
 But getting up and climbing is better than not climbing at all,

110
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:43,000
 because we're not after safe, we're after courageous faithfulness.

111
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:47,000
 So tonight, how do we move away from a life of safe and into a life of courageous faithfulness?

